## 5. Risks and Assumptions

### 5.1 Risks

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Risk | Impact | Likelihood | Mitigation |
| Retry loops increase LLM token consumption | Medium | High | Cap at 2 retries; track token usage per retry cycle |
| Verify node adds latency to every agent execution | Medium | Medium | Verify criteria should be lightweight; consider parallel verification for non-blocking checks |
| Strategy switch alternate prompts not well-defined per node | High | Medium | Define alternate strategies as part of implementation; default to human intervention if not configured |
| Infinite loop if verify → retry → verify cycle has a bug | High | Low | Hard cap on verify attempts (maxVerifyAttempts=2); integration tests for the cycle |
| Exponential backoff delays may exceed node timeout | Low | Low | Validate total retry time < NODE\_TIMEOUT\_MS before starting retry loop |

### 5.2 Assumptions

* The existing retryCount field in PipelineState is sufficient for tracking retry state (no schema migration needed)
* LLM providers support the same API for retried calls (no session/context issues)
* The StreamHandler.emitStatus() pattern can be extended for new event types without breaking existing consumers
* Alternate strategy prompts will be defined in configuration files, not hardcoded in node implementations
* The existing graph structure (conditional edges) can accommodate verify nodes without requiring a full graph rebuild

## 6. Non-Functional Requirements

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Category | Requirement | Details |
| Performance | Retry backoff must not exceed total node timeout | Total retry time (initial + 1s + 2s = 3s overhead max) well within 300s timeout |
| Performance | Verify node must complete within 30s | Verification should be a quick LLM call or rule-based check |
| Reliability | Self-correction must not introduce data corruption | Each retry starts fresh; no partial state from failed attempts persisted |
| Observability | All self-correction actions must emit stream events | UI can track retry count, verify status, strategy changes in real-time |
| Testability | 100% path coverage for retry/verify/switch logic | Unit tests with mocked LLM and MCP |
| Scalability | Patterns apply uniformly to all agent nodes | BaseNode implements retry; VerifyNode is generic and reusable |
| Maintainability | Verify criteria and alternate strategies are configurable | Not hardcoded; can be updated without code changes |

